<text id="02-output-contract" title="PMBoK 8 Six Core Principles Output Contract" version="1.1.0" est_tokens="800" depth="essential">
  <summary>JSON Schema (draft-07) for the checklist artefact this methodology produces. The validator script enforces the schema.</summary>

  <section title="Schema">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "$id": "https://faion.net/schemas/six-core-principles.json",
  "title": "PMBoK 8 Six Core Principles",
  "type": "object",
  "required": [
    "__faion_header__",
    "items"
  ],
  "properties": {
    "__faion_header__": {
      "type": "object",
      "required": [
        "methodology",
        "version",
        "produces",
        "rules_satisfied"
      ],
      "properties": {
        "methodology": {
          "const": "six-core-principles"
        },
        "version": {
          "const": "1.1.0"
        },
        "produces": {
          "const": "checklist"
        },
        "rules_satisfied": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "enum": [
              "positive-evidence-required",
              "fail-blocks-gate",
              "canonical-six-names",
              "sustainability-numeric-proxy",
              "pin-pmbok-edition"
            ]
          },
          "minItems": 1
        }
      }
    },
    "items": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": [
          "id",
          "status",
          "evidence"
        ],
        "properties": {
          "id": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "status": {
            "enum": [
              "pass",
              "fail",
              "na"
            ]
          },
          "evidence": {
            "type": "string",
            "minLength": 5
          }
        }
      },
      "minItems": 1
    }
  }
}
]]></code>
  </section>

  <section title="Forbidden patterns">
    <list>
      <item>Missing __faion_header__ block — every artefact MUST carry methodology, version, produces, rules_satisfied.</item>
      <item>rules_satisfied containing IDs outside the six-core-principles rule set.</item>
      <item>Empty top-level body (no sections / data / entries / items / criteria) — the artefact must carry payload, not metadata only.</item>
      <item>Free-form prose substituted for the typed sub-fields the schema requires.</item>
    </list>
  </section>

  <example valid="true">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "__faion_header__": {
    "methodology": "six-core-principles",
    "version": "1.1.0",
    "produces": "checklist",
    "rules_satisfied": [
      "positive-evidence-required",
      "fail-blocks-gate",
      "canonical-six-names"
    ]
  },
  "items": [
    {
      "id": "C1",
      "status": "pass",
      "evidence": "verified by sign-off 2026-05-23"
    }
  ]
}
]]></code>
    <note>Header carries methodology + version + produces + rules_satisfied; body matches the per-produces shape.</note>
  </example>

  <example valid="false">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "artefact_path": "docs/six-core-principles.md"
}
]]></code>
    <note>Header missing → validator rejects; rules_satisfied not declared → no audit trail.</note>
  </example>

  <reference path="scripts/validate-six-core-principles.py">Validator script</reference>
</text>
